    <p class="text-gray-300">&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;Gate equivalent is a measure for area requirements of integrated circuits (IC). It is derived by dividing the area of the IC by the area of a two-input NAND gate with the lowest driving strength.</p>

