    <p class="text-gray-300">Finally, we advised the compiler to use the /O2 option for the speed optimized profiles I, III and V.</p>

    <h2 id="sec-66" class="text-2xl font-bold"><strong>Size optimized implementation</strong></h2>

    <p class="text-gray-300">For profiles II, IV and VI we implemented the key schedule similar to the 16-bit size optimized implementation. However, since we operate on 64-bit variables (__int64) we use the 4 × 64 S-box S4×&lt;sup&gt;64&lt;/sup&gt; which was introduced above. The permutation layer was implemented using the arithmetic description (see Section 4.3.3). Furthermore we advised the compiler to use the /O1 option for the code size optimized profiles II, IV and VI.</p>

